<H4 ALIGN=CENTER>
	<B>
	<FONT SIZE=+1>OMNICAM:&nbsp;OMNIDIRECTIONAL&nbsp;VIDEO&nbsp;CAMERA
	</FONT>
	</B>
</H4>

<P>
The <!WA0><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/CAVE"> Computer Vision Laboratory
</A> of the <!WA1><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/"> Department of Computer
Science</A> at <!WA2><A HREF="http://www.columbia.edu/">Columbia University </A>
introduces <B>OMNICAM</B>, a video camera that can &quot;see&quot; 
in all directions.

The optics of the sensor has been designed to ensure that all points in
the world are projected through a single center of projection. This allows
the <B>OMNIVIDEO </B>software to generate pure perspective images at video
rate for any user-selected viewing direction and magnification.
</P>

<CENTER>
<P>
	<!WA3><IMG SRC="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~venkat/omnipage/31.jpg" HEIGHT=200 WIDTH=150 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>
</P>
</CENTER>

<P>
Come to the entrance of the Computer Science Department at 450 Mudd
Hall to interact with <B>OMNICAM </B>and <B>OMNIVIDEO</B>!
</P>

